# Identifiers

Identifiers must use only ASCII letters, digits and the "$" sign.

| Style                                 | Category                                                           |
| ------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------ |
| `UpperCamelCase`                      | class / interface / type / enum / mixin / module                   |
| `lowerCamelCase`                      | variable / parameter / function / method / property / module alias |
| `CONSTANT_CASE`                       | angular injection tokens                                           |
| `#ident`                              | private identifiers                                                |
| Finnish notation (lowerCamelCase + $) | RxJS observables                                                   |

Even though `CONSTANT_CASE` is commonly used to refer to values that should be not be modified and gen AI usually applies this convention we will obviate and will reserve this convention exclusively for [Angular injection tokens](https://angular.dev/api/core/InjectionToken).

```ts
const SOME_TOKEN = new InjectionToken<MyInterface>('SomeToken');
```

The naming style should be precise and descriptive at the same time.

Do not suffix the name with the type or the symbol type, since it is redundant:

```ts
// WRONG
searchSubject = new Subject<string>();
export enum EnvironmentEnum {
  local,
  dev,
  stag,
  prod,
}

// RIGHT
search$ = new Subject<string>();
export enum Environment {
  local,
  dev,
  stag,
  prod,
}
```

Do not use leading or trailing underscore.

```ts
// WRONG
_privateProperty = 'value';
publicProperty_ = 'value';
__internalMethod() {}

// RIGHT
#privateProperty = 'value';
publicProperty = 'value';
internalMethod() {}
```

Do not prefix interfaces with "I".

```ts
// WRONG
export interface ICode {}

// RIGHT
export interface Code {}
```

Always prefix booleans with "has" and "is".

```ts
// WRONG
loading: boolean = false;
disabled: boolean = true;
children: boolean = false;
errors: boolean = true;

// RIGHT
isLoading: boolean = false;
isDisabled: boolean = true;
hasChildren: boolean = false;
hasErrors: boolean = true;
```
